&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keoladeo National Park&lt;/strong&gt; serves as the location for the endangered migratory bird Siberian Crane.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Keoladeo Ghana National Park, also known as Bharatpur National Park, is a wildlife sanctuary located south of the city of Bharatpur in the eastern Rajasthan state in northwest India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Suraj Mal, the maharaja of the princely state of Bharatpur, established it as a hunting preserve in the late 19th century.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A bird sanctuary was established there in 1956.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was renamed Keoladeo in honour of the historic temple in the park devoted to the Hindu god Shiva when it was made a national park in 1981.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thus we know that t&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;he Siberian Crane, an endangered migratory bird is a regular visitor of Keoladeo National Park.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is option &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;, i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Madhya Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

